                  <m:mrow/>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
  
            
       </m:math>
        </equation></para><para id="import-auto-id2366999">Now, observe <link target-id="import-auto-id1561864"/>. You can use trigonometry to determine the magnitude of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>L</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>R</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>. Notice that:</para><para id="import-auto-id1444650"><equation id="eip-id2130931"><m:math>
            
