                        <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>5.0º</m:mn>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                        <m:mo>.</m:mo>
  
  
  </m:mtd>
  
                    </m:mtr>
                  </m:mtable>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>          
          </m:math>
        </equation></para><para id="import-auto-id1541279">Now, we can substitute the values for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>L</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>R</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>, into the net force equation in the vertical direction:</para><para id="import-auto-id2079675"><equation id="eip-id2085200"><m:math>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mtable columnalign="left">
                    <m:mtr>
  
  <m:mtd>
  
                                <m:msub>
